- A quarter note takes up the duration of one beat in a 4/4 time signature.
- A whole note takes up the duration of two beats in a 4/4 time signature.
- An eighth note takes up the duration of half a beat in a 4/4 time signature.
- A half note takes up the duration of two half beats in a 4/4 time signature.

- Quarter notes: 4 x 1 = 4
- Eighth notes: 3 x 2 = 3
- Sixteenth notes: 5 x 4 = 20
- Whole notes: 2 x 4 = 8
Total beats = 4 + 3 + 20 + 8 = 35 beats

Total measures = Total beats/Number of beats in a measure x Number of beats in a measure = 35/4 x 4 = 20 measures

The note tempo values take up 20 measures given the given Time Signature.
